
[1]rightfulness

   RIGHTFULNESS, n.

   1. Justice; accordance with the rules of right; as the rightfulness of
   a claim to lands or tenements.

   2. Moral rectitude.

   But still although we fail of perfect rightfulness. [Not usual.]
